 Japan's most successful PSP title, Monster Hunter Portable 2G, is heading to
 Europe and US. Renamed Monster Hunter Freedom Unite, this latest installment
 in the epic Monster Hunter series delivers over 500 hours of gameplay spanning
 some 400 missions. Added with previously unreleased monsters, weapons and
 missions and you have the biggest Monster Hunter game to date. Using the Ad-Hoc
 connection players can adventure with up to three friends for a savaging
 multiplayer hunting party. From devising the strategy to executing the attack,
 players will need to work together in order to hunt down the ferocious beasts
 and progress through the wide range of quests on offer. Players will be rewarded
 for their use of deep fighting combat systems, encouraging them to seek out the
 more experienced hunters and team up in order to learn from their experience.
 Even in single player mode Hunters won't be alone thanks to the introduction of
 the new AI Felyne feature. Accompanying players on quests your furry ally will
